Santa Cristina de Lena.label: Santa Cristina de Lena
Santa Cristina de Lena.description: St Christine of Lena is a Roman Catholic Asturian pre-Romanesque church located in the Lena municipality, about 25 km south of Oviedo, Spain, on an old Roman road that joined the lands of the plateau with Asturias. Wikipedia

Basilica di San Marino.label: Basilica di San Marino
Basilica di San Marino.description: The Basilica di San Marino is a Catholic church located in the Republic of San Marino. While the country has a distinct domination of historic religious buildings of Christian faith, the basilica is the main church of the City of San Marino. Wikipedia

Dohány Street Synagogue.label: Dohány Street Synagogue
Dohány Street Synagogue.description: The Dohány Street Synagogue, also known as The Great Synagogue or Tabakgasse Synagogue, is located in Erzsébetváros, the 7th district of Budapest. It is the largest synagogue in Europe and one of the largest in the world. Wikipedia

Dormition of the Theotokos Cathedral, Cl.label: Dormition of the Theotokos Cathedral, Cluj-Napoca
Dormition of the Theotokos Cathedral, Cl.description: The Dormition of the Theotokos Cathedral is the most famous Romanian Orthodox church of Cluj-Napoca, Romania. Wikipedia

Bajrakli Mosque, Belgrade.label: Bajrakli Mosque, Belgrade
Bajrakli Mosque, Belgrade.description: The Bajrakli Mosque is a mosque in Belgrade, the capital of Serbia. It is located in Gospodar Jevremova Street in the neighbourhood of Dorćol. Wikipedia

Grundtvig's Church.label: Grundtvig's Church
Grundtvig's Church.description: Grundtvig's Church is located in the Bispebjerg district of Copenhagen, Denmark. It is a rare example of expressionist church architecture. Due to its unusual appearance, it is one of the best known churches in the city. Wikipedia

Cathedral of Saint John the Divine.label: Cathedral of Saint John the Divine
Cathedral of Saint John the Divine.description: The Cathedral of St. John the Divine, officially the Cathedral Church of Saint John The Great Divine in the City and Diocese of New York, is the cathedral of the Episcopal Diocese of New York. Wikipedia

Luis de Torres Synagogue.label: Luis de Torres Synagogue
Luis de Torres Synagogue.description: Luis De Torres Synagogue is the only synagogue in the Bahamas. Named after Luis de Torres, a Jewish Marrano who sailed with Christopher Columbus to the new world, it is situated between two churches. Wikipedia

Mogadishu Cathedral.label: Mogadishu Cathedral
Mogadishu Cathedral.description: Mogadishu Cathedral is a Roman Catholic cathedral located in Mogadishu, Somalia. When still operational, it served as the seat of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Mogadiscio. In 2013, the Diocese announced plans to refurbish the building. Wikipedia

Las Lajas Sanctuary.label: Las Lajas Sanctuary
Las Lajas Sanctuary.description: Las Lajas Sanctuary is a basilica church located in the southern Colombian Department of Nariño, municipality of Ipiales and built inside the canyon of the Guáitara River. Wikipedia

Old St. Peter's Basilica.label: Old St. Peter's Basilica
Old St. Peter's Basilica.description: Old St. Peter's Basilica was the building that stood, from the 4th to 16th centuries, on the spot where the St. Peter's Basilica stands today in Vatican City. Wikipedia

St. John's Cathedral (Antigua and Barbud.label: St. John's Cathedral
St. John's Cathedral (Antigua and Barbud.description: St. John's Cathedral also known as the St. John the Divine, the Cathedral Church of the Diocese of North Eastern Caribbean and Aruba, is an Anglican church perched on a hilltop in St. John's, Antigua and Barbuda. Wikipedia

Saint Petersburg Mosque.label: Saint Petersburg Mosque
Saint Petersburg Mosque.description: The Saint Petersburg Mosque, when opened in 1913, was the largest mosque in Europe outside Turkey, its minarets 49 meters in height and the dome is 39 meters high. The mosque is situated in downtown St Petersburg. Wikipedia

St Francis Xavier's Cathedral, Adelaide.label: St Francis Xavier's Cathedral, Adelaide
St Francis Xavier's Cathedral, Adelaide.description: St Francis Xavier's Cathedral is a Roman Catholic cathedral in Adelaide, South Australia. It is classified as being a Gothic Revival building in the Early English style. The tower stands 36 m high and is 56.5 m lengthwise and 29.5 m horizontally. Wikipedia

St. Mark's Church, Belgrade.label: St. Mark's Church, Belgrade
St. Mark's Church, Belgrade.description: St. Mark's Church or Church of St. Mark is a Serbian Orthodox church located in the Tašmajdan park in Belgrade, Serbia, near the Parliament of Serbia. Wikipedia

White Mosque (Nazareth).label: White Mosque, Nazareth
White Mosque (Nazareth).description: The White Mosque is the oldest mosque in Nazareth, Israel and is located in Harat Alghama or the "Mosque Quarter" in the center of Nazareth's Old Market. Wikipedia

Adolf Fredriks kyrka.label: Adolf Fredrik Church
Adolf Fredriks kyrka.description: Adolf Fredrik Church is a church in central Stockholm, Sweden, named after Adolf Frederick. It was built in 1768-1774, replacing a wooden chapel from 1674, which was dedicated to Saint Olof. Wikipedia

St. Michael's Cathedral, Qingdao.label: St. Michael's Cathedral, Qingdao
St. Michael's Cathedral, Qingdao.description: St. Michael's Cathedral，also called the Zhejiang Road Catholic Church（浙江路天主教堂），which is abbreviated by locals to simply the "Catholic Church" (天主教堂）is a Catholic church in Qingdao, Shandong Province, China and is the seat of the Bishop of the Roman ... Wikipedia

Votive Church, Vienna.label: Votive Church, Vienna
Votive Church, Vienna.description: The Votive Church is a neo-Gothic church located on the Ringstraße in Vienna, Austria. Following the attempted assassination of Emperor Franz Joseph in 1853, the Emperor's brother Archduke Ferdinand ... Wikipedia

Lapua Cathedral.label: Lapua Cathedral
Lapua Cathedral.description: The Lapua Cathedral is a church in Lapua, Finland, and the seat of the Diocese of Lapua. The neoclassical cathedral was designed by Carl Ludvig Engel and built in 1827. The cathedral's pipe organ is the largest in Finland. Wikipedia

Katarina Church.label: Katarina Church
Katarina Church.description: Katarina kyrka is one of the major churches in central Stockholm, Sweden. The original building was constructed 1656–1695. It has been rebuilt twice after being destroyed by fires, the second time during the 1990s. Wikipedia

Neue Kirche, Berlin.label: Neue Kirche, Berlin
Neue Kirche, Berlin.description: The Neue Kirche, is located in Berlin on the Gendarmenmarkt across from French Church of Friedrichstadt. Wikipedia

Tallinn Synagogue.label: Tallinn Synagogue
Tallinn Synagogue.description: Tallinn Synagogue, also known as Beit Bella Synagogue, is located in Estonia’s capital city. The privately funded synagogue in central Tallinn was inaugurated on May 16, 2007. Wikipedia

St. Nicholas' Church, Berlin.label: St. Nicholas' Church, Berlin
St. Nicholas' Church, Berlin.description: The St. Nikolai-Kirche, is the oldest church in Berlin, the capital of Germany. The church is located in the eastern part of central Berlin, the borough of Mitte. Wikipedia

Turku Synagogue.label: Turku Synagogue
Turku Synagogue.description: Turku Synagogue in the city of Turku is one of the two synagogues in Finland. Located in the VII District, the synagogue is used by the Jewish community of Turku. Wikipedia

Cristo de la Concordia.label: Cristo de la Concordia
Cristo de la Concordia.description: Cristo de la Concordia is a statue of Jesus Christ located atop San Pedro Hill, to the east of Cochabamba, Bolivia. It is accessible by cable car, or by climbing 2,000 steps. Wikipedia

El Ghriba synagogue.label: El Ghriba synagogue
El Ghriba synagogue.description: The ancient El Ghriba Synagogue, also known as the Djerba Synagogue, is located on the Tunisian island of Djerba. It is situated in the Jewish village of Hara Seghira, several kilometres southwest of Houmt Souk, the capital of Djerba. Wikipedia

Great Synagogue (Tel Aviv).label: Great Synagogue, Tel Aviv
Great Synagogue (Tel Aviv).description: The Great Synagogue of Tel Aviv is located on 110 Allenby Street, Tel Aviv, just east of the Shalom Tower. The building was designed by Yehuda Magidovitch in 1922 and completed in 1926. It was renovated in 1970 with a new external facade of arches. Wikipedia

Nożyk Synagogue.label: Nożyk Synagogue
Nożyk Synagogue.description: The Nożyk Synagogue is the only surviving prewar Jewish house of prayer in Warsaw, Poland. It was built in 1898-1902 and was restored after World War II. Wikipedia

Ringebu Stave Church.label: Ringebu Stave Church
Ringebu Stave Church.description: Ringebu Stave Church is a stave church located in Ringebu in Ringebu municipality, Gudbrandsdal, Norway. Built in the first quarter of the 13th century, and dated according to coins found during archeologic surveys. Wikipedia

Ramban Synagogue.label: Ramban Synagogue
Ramban Synagogue.description: The Ramban Synagogue, is the second oldest active synagogue in the Old City of Jerusalem. It was founded by Nahmanides in 1267. Today it is located at the corner of Ha-Yehudim Street and the square in the Jewish Quarter. Wikipedia

Santa Maria presso San Satiro.label: Santa Maria presso San Satiro
Santa Maria presso San Satiro.description:
Santa Maria presso San Satiro is a church of Milan.
The church lies on the site of a primitive worship place erected by the archbishop Anspertus in 879, dedicated to Saint Satyrus, confessor and brother of Saints Ambrose and Marcellina. Wikipedia

Roonstrasse Synagogue.label: Roonstrasse Synagogue
Roonstrasse Synagogue.description: Roonstrasse Synagogue, located in Cologne, Germany, is one of the five pre-Nazi synagogues of the locality, which was destroyed on November 9, 1938 during nation-wide attacks on Jewish-owned property when Germany was under Nazi rule. Wikipedia

Baitus Sami.label: Baitus Sami
Baitus Sami.description: Baitus Sami Mosque is located in the German city of Hannover, Lower Saxony. The Baitus Sami is the first and currently the "only mosque in Hanover with a dome and minaret." Wikipedia

Ashkenazi Synagogue of Istanbul.label: Ashkenazi Synagogue of Istanbul
Ashkenazi Synagogue of Istanbul.description: The Ashkenazi Synagogue is an Ashkenazi synagogue located near the Galata Tower in Karaköy neighborhood of Beyoğlu in Istanbul, Turkey. It is the only currently active Ashkenazi synagogue in Istanbul open to visits and prayers. Wikipedia

St. Peter's Church, Copenhagen.label: St. Peter's Church, Copenhagen
St. Peter's Church, Copenhagen.description: St. Peter's Church is the parish church of the German-speaking community in Copenhagen, Denmark. Built as a single-nave church in the mid-15th century, it is the oldest building in central Copenhagen. Wikipedia

Cathedral of All Saints, Albany, New Yor.label: Cathedral of All Saints, Albany, New York
Cathedral of All Saints, Albany, New Yor.description: The Cathedral of All Saints, Albany, New York is located on Elk Street in central Albany, New York, United States. It is the central church of the Albany and the seat of the Episcopal Bishop of Albany. Wikipedia

Dolní Kounice Synagogue.label: Dolní Kounice Synagogue
Dolní Kounice Synagogue.description: The first traces of Jewish settlement in Dolní Kounice are from half of 15th century. First written note comes from 1581. Wikipedia

Great Mosque of Hama.label: Great Mosque of Hama
Great Mosque of Hama.description: The Great Mosque of Hama, is a mosque in Hama, Syria. It is located about 400 meters west of the citadel. Built in the 8th century CE, it was heavily damaged in a 1982 uprising, but today it has been completely restored. Wikipedia

Hyde Park Reformed Dutch Church.label: Hyde Park Reformed Dutch Church
Hyde Park Reformed Dutch Church.description: Hyde Park Dutch Reformed Church is located on US 9 in the center of Hyde Park, New York, United States, just north of the post office and the junction with Market Street at the center of town. It is a complex of several buildings on a 2-acre lot. Wikipedia

Hirami Ahmet Pasha Mosque.label: Hirami Ahmet Pasha Mosque
Hirami Ahmet Pasha Mosque.description: Hirami Ahmet Pasha Mosque is a former Eastern Orthodox church converted into a mosque by the Ottomans. The small church, one among the 36 dedicated to Saint John the Baptist in Constantinople, was part of a monastery bearing the same name. Wikipedia

Nasrullah Mosque.label: Nasrullah Mosque
Nasrullah Mosque.description: Nasrullah Mosque is a 16th-century Ottoman mosque in Kastamonu, Turkey. Wikipedia

Saint Gevorg of Mughni Church, Tbilisi.label: Saint Gevork of Mughni Church, Tbilisi
Saint Gevorg of Mughni Church, Tbilisi.description: The Saint Gevork of Mughni Church also known as Saint George of Mughni Church is a 13th-century Armenian church in Tbilisi, Georgia that was entirely rebuilt in 1756. Wikipedia

San Filippo Neri (Genoa).label: San Filippo Neri
San Filippo Neri (Genoa).description: San Filippo Neri is a Baroque church on via Lomellini in central Genoa. The order of the Oratory of Saint Philip Neri had arrived in Genoa in 1643, under the sponsorship of the Oratorian and Marchese Camillo Pallavicini who was born in Genoa. Wikipedia

San Sebastian Church, Madrid.label: San Sebastian Church, Madrid
San Sebastian Church, Madrid.description: The Saint Sebastian Church or Iglesia de San Sebastián is a 16th-century church in central Madrid, Spain. It is located on Atocha street, #39. Wikipedia

Sanctuary of Las Nazarenas.label: Sanctuary of Las Nazarenas
Sanctuary of Las Nazarenas.description: The Sanctuary of Las Nazarenas is a church in Lima and is the site of the Peruvian catholic procession of the Lord of Miracles, Señor de los Milagros, who is also the patron of the city. Wikipedia

Sant'Andrea Forisportam (Pisa).label: Sant'Andrea Forisportam
Sant'Andrea Forisportam (Pisa).description:
Sant'Andrea Forisportam is a church building, now deconsecrated, in Pisa, Tuscany, Italy.
A church on the site is documented as early as 1104, the name deriving from its location outside a gate of the walls of medieval Pisa. Wikipedia

San Bartolomeo, Venice.label: San Bartolomeo, Venice
San Bartolomeo, Venice.description: San Bartolomeo is a church in Venice, Italy. It is near the Rialto Bridge in the sestiere, or neighborhood, of San Marco. Wikipedia
San Bartolomeo, Venice.Address: Calle dell'Orso, 5494, 30124 San Marco ,Venezia VE, Italy

Santi Nazaro e Celso (Brescia).label: Santi Nazaro e Celso, Brescia
Santi Nazaro e Celso (Brescia).description: The church of Santi Nazaro e Celso is located on Corso Giamcomo Matteotti, at the intersection with Cia Fratelli Bronzetti, in Brescia, Lombardy, Italy. Wikipedia

Sheikh Ali al-Bakka Mosque.label: Sheikh Ali al-Bakka Mosque
Sheikh Ali al-Bakka Mosque.description: Sheikh Ali al-Bakka Mosque is a 13th-century mosque in the northwestern section of the Old City of Hebron in the southern West Bank. Wikipedia

St James, Norton.label: St James, Norton
St James, Norton.description:
St James' Church lies in the Norton district of Sheffield, South Yorkshire, England.
Although the village of Norton was recorded in the Domesday Book, no church was noted. Wikipedia

Mahmood Mosque, Zurich.label: Mahmood Mosque, Zürich
Mahmood Mosque, Zurich.description: The Mahmood Mosque, situated in Forchstrasse, Zurich, is the first purpose-built mosque in Switzerland. It ia owned and run by the Ahmadiyya Muslim Community. Wikipedia

Cathedral of Jaca.label: Jaca Cathedral
Cathedral of Jaca.description:
The Cathedral of St Peter the Apostle is the cathedral church of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Jaca located in Jaca, province of Huesca, Spain.
It is the first Romanesque cathedral built in Aragon and one of the oldest in the Iberian peninsula. Wikipedia

Faith Episcopal Church.label: Faith Episcopal Church
Faith Episcopal Church.description: Faith Episcopal Church is located in Cameron Park, California, United States, just off of U.S. Route 50 in the California Gold Country foothills region. Parishioners come from Sacramento, Folsom, El Dorado Hills and the Placerville area. Wikipedia

Free Synagogue of Flushing.label: Free Synagogue of Flushing
Free Synagogue of Flushing.description: The Free Synagogue of Flushing is a Reform synagogue in the Flushing neighborhood of Queens, New York City. It is the oldest liberal Reform congregation in Queens. Wikipedia

Gökmedrese.label: Gökmedrese
Gökmedrese.description: Gökmedrese or Gök Medrese, aka Sahibiye Medresesi, is a 13th-century medrese, an Islamic educational institution, in Sivas, Turkey. Wikipedia

Hajib Shakarbar.label: Hajib Shakarbar
Hajib Shakarbar.description: Hazrat Hajib Shakarbar was born as the younger of the two sons of Hazrat Shams Tabrizi and Hazrat Shams Sabzwari in 1213 AC. Wikipedia

Iglesia de San Bartolomé de Barva.label: Iglesia de San Bartolomé de Barva
Iglesia de San Bartolomé de Barva.description: The Iglesia de San Bartolomé de Barva is a church in Barva, Costa Rica. The first church was established between 1568 and 1575, and dedicated to Saint Bartholomew; it is rumored to have been built on an indigenous burial ground. Wikipedia

Loughwood Meeting House.label: Loughwood Meeting House
Loughwood Meeting House.description: Loughwood Meeting House is a historic Baptist chapel located 1 mile south of the village of Dalwood, Devon, England. Wikipedia

Mohabbat Khan Mosque.label: Mohabbat Khan Mosque
Mohabbat Khan Mosque.description: The Mahabat Khan Mosque is a 17th-century mosque in Peshawar, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan. It is named after the Mughal governor of Peshawar Nawab Mahabat Khan who served under Emperors Shah Jehan and ... Wikipedia

Notre Dame de l'Assomption, les Saintes.label: Notre Dame de l'Assomption, les Saintes
Notre Dame de l'Assomption, les Saintes.description: Notre-Dame de l'Assomption is a Roman Catholic Church of the archipelago of Îles des Saintes, a dependency of the French Overseas department of Guadeloupe. It is located in rue Jean Calot in Fond-du-Curé, a quartier of Terre-de-Haut Island. Wikipedia

Old Cathedral of Cuenca.label: Old Cathedral of Cuenca
Old Cathedral of Cuenca.description: The Church of the Shrine — commonly referred to as the Old Cathedral of Cuenca — was the main place of Spanish worship during the time of Spanish colonization in Cuenca, Ecuador. Wikipedia

San Martino (Pisa).label: San Martino
San Martino (Pisa).description:
San Martino is a church in Pisa, Italy, facing piazza San Martino, on the left bank of the Arno river.
Documents from 1067 cite a church of "San Martino in Guazzolongo", belonging to the Augustinian order. Wikipedia

Sant'Antonio da Padova in Via Tuscolana.label: Sant'Antonio da Padova in Via Tuscolana
Sant'Antonio da Padova in Via Tuscolana.description: The Church of Saint Anthony of Padua on Via Tuscolana is a Roman Catholic titular church in Rome, built for the religious congregation of the Rogationists of the Heart of Jesus, to whose founder Saint ... Wikipedia

Second Baptist Church (Poughkeepsie, New.label: Second Baptist Church
Second Baptist Church (Poughkeepsie, New.description: The Second Baptist Church in Poughkeepsie, New York, United States, is located at the corner of Vassar and Mill streets. Wikipedia

All Saints Episcopal Church (Appleton, W.label: All Saints Episcopal Church
All Saints Episcopal Church (Appleton, W.description: All Saints Episcopal Church is a historic Episcopal church in Appleton, Wisconsin. A parish in the Diocese of Fond du Lac, it is the only Episcopal church in Appleton. The congregation first met circa 1854 and organized in 1856. Wikipedia

Brighton Friends Meeting House.label: Brighton Friends Meeting House
Brighton Friends Meeting House.description: The Brighton Friends Meeting House is a Friends meeting house in the centre of Brighton, part of the city of Brighton and Hove in East Sussex, England. Wikipedia

Cathedral of St. John the Evangelist (Sp.label: Cathedral of Saint John the Evangelist

Domus Galilaeae.label: Domus Galilaeae
Domus Galilaeae.description: Domus Galilaeae or House of Galilee, located on the peak of Mount of Beatitudes, above and north of Capernaum and the Sea of Galilee, is a Christian meeting place used for seminars and conventions. Wikipedia

Saint Anne Catholic Church of the Byzant.label: Saint Anne Byzantine Catholic Church
Saint Anne Catholic Church of the Byzant.description: Saint Anne Byzantine Catholic Church is a Catholic Christian parish of the Byzantine Ruthenian Tradition located in the City of San Luis Obispo, California. It was founded in 1986. Wikipedia

St Chad's Church, Far Headingley.label: St Chad's Church, Far Headingley
St Chad's Church, Far Headingley.description: St Chad's Church, Far Headingley is the parish church of Far Headingley in Leeds, West Yorkshire, England. The dedication is to Chad of Mercia, who was bishop of York and died in AD 672. Wikipedia

St Mary's Church, Blymhill.label: St Mary's Church, Blymhill
St Mary's Church, Blymhill.description: St. Mary's Church, Blymhill is an Anglican church in the village of Blymhill, Staffordshire, England. The building, which is a Grade I listed building, was constructed in the 14th century and restored and extended in the 18th and 19th centuries. Wikipedia

Agha Bozorg Mosque.label: Agha Bozorg mosque
Agha Bozorg Mosque.description: Agha Bozorg mosque is a historical mosque in Kashan, Iran. The mosque was built in the late 18th century by master-mimar Ustad Haj Sa'ban-ali, the mosque and theological school is located in the center of Kāshān. Wikipedia

Baitul Huda, Usingen.label: Baitul Huda, Usingen
Baitul Huda, Usingen.description:
The Baitul Huda in Usingen is a mosque in Germany run by the Ahmadiyya Muslim Community and was inaugurated on September 7, 2004 by Mirza Masroor Ahmad.
Its two prayer rooms are 77 m² each. The community in Usingen has 160 members. Wikipedia

Central Synagogue of Aleppo.label: Central Synagogue of Aleppo
Central Synagogue of Aleppo.description: The Central Synagogue of Aleppo, also known as the Great Synagogue of Aleppo, Joab's Synagogue or Al-Bandara Synagogue, has been a Jewish place of worship since the 5th century C.E. Wikipedia

Chodae Community Church.label: Chodae Community Church
Chodae Community Church.description: Chodae Community Church, formerly called Cho Dae Presbyterian Church, is a Korean Presbytery Church located in Norwood, New Jersey. The church, founded in 1986, has several different ministries catering to people of different cultures and languages. Wikipedia

Didsbury Mosque.label: Didsbury Mosque
Didsbury Mosque.description: The Didsbury Mosque and Islamic Centre is located on Burton Road, West Didsbury in Manchester, England. Wikipedia

Islamic Society of Western Maryland.label: Islamic Society of Western Maryland
Islamic Society of Western Maryland.description: The Islamic Society of Western Maryland, located in Hagerstown, Maryland is the first permanent structure to be built specifically to serve as a mosque in Western Maryland. Wikipedia

Jami Mosque.label: Jami Mosque, Toronto
Jami Mosque.description: Located just east of High Park in Toronto, Jami Mosque is the oldest Canadian Islamic centre in the city and dubbed "the mother of all the mosques in Toronto". Wikipedia

Küçük Mecidiye Mosque.label: Küçük Mecidiye Mosque
Küçük Mecidiye Mosque.description: The Küçük Mecidiye Mosque is an Ottoman mosque in the Beşiktaş district of Istanbul, Turkey. It was built from the order of Sultan Abdülmecid I by Nigoğos Balyan, member of the Balyan family. Wikipedia

Kotla Mubarakpur Complex.label: Kotla Mubarakpur Complex
Kotla Mubarakpur Complex.description: Kotla Mubarakpur Complex, a medieval village, is now an upscale market place with a residential colony in South Delhi. The village Kotla Mubarakpur dominates Bainsla gotra of Gurjars, India. Wikipedia

Maribor Synagogue.label: Maribor Synagogue
Maribor Synagogue.description: Maribor Synagogue is a former synagogue and current museum in the city of Maribor, Slovenia. Located in what was the center of the medieval Maribor ghetto Židovska ulica, it is one of the oldest preserved ... Wikipedia

Nakhalpara Sapra Mosque.label: Nakhalpara Sapra Mosque
Nakhalpara Sapra Mosque.description: Nakhalpara Sapra Mosque is a mosque in Nakhalpara, Bangladesh. Wikipedia

Sandys Row Synagogue.label: Sandys Row Synagogue
Sandys Row Synagogue.description: Sandy's Row Synagogue is a historic Grade II listed synagogue in the East End of London. Wikipedia

St. John the Baptist Church, Židikai.label: St. John the Baptist Church, Židikai
St. John the Baptist Church, Židikai.description: St. John the Baptist Church is a Roman Catholic church in Židikai, Lithuania. It is located in the west of Mažeikiai district municipality, near the road Mažeikiai-Skuodas. Wikipedia

St Winefride's, Sandbach.label: St Winefride's, Sandbach
St Winefride's, Sandbach.description: St Winefride’s is a Catholic church in Sandbach, Cheshire, England within the Roman Catholic Diocese of Shrewsbury. The Church is a Member of Churches Together in Sandbach Wikipedia

Santuario de San Jose.label: Santuario de San Jose
Santuario de San Jose.description: Santuario de San Jose is a parish church found inside the Green Hills East Village in Mandaluyong City, Philippines. It is designated as the Shrine of Saint Joseph the Patriarch. It is run by the Oblates of St. Joseph. Wikipedia

Shavnabada Monastery.label: Shavnabada Monastery
Shavnabada Monastery.description: Shavnabada Monastery is a medieval Georgian Orthodox monastic complex that is located upon Shavnabada Mountain, approximately 8 km away from the village of Tabatskuri and 20 km southeast of Bakuriani, in the Samtskhe-Javakheti Province, of Georgia. Wikipedia

St. Jude Melkite Catholic Church.label: St. Jude Melkite Catholic Church
St. Jude Melkite Catholic Church.description: St Jude Melkite Catholic Church is a Melkite Greek Catholic Church in Brickell in Miami, Florida.It is located at 126 SE Fifteenth Road, Miami, FL 33129. It is part of the Melkite Greek Catholic church under the Eparchy of Newton. Wikipedia

Church of the Gesù.label: Church of the Gesù
Church of the Gesù.description: The Church of the Gesù is the mother church of the Society of Jesus, a Roman Catholic religious order also known as the Jesuits. Wikipedia

St. Lucia's Cathedral.label: St. Lucia's Cathedral
St. Lucia's Cathedral.description: A replica of St. Peter’s Basilica in the Vatican, St. Lucia's Cathedral is the seat of the archbishop of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Colombo in Sri Lanka. Wikipedia

Umm al-Naser Mosque.label: Umm al-Nasr Mosque
Umm al-Naser Mosque.description: Umm al-Nasr Mosque or Beit Hanoun Mosque is the oldest mosque in the Palestinian city of Beit Hanoun in the Gaza Strip, located in the center of the city. Wikipedia

Christ the King Cathedral (Gaborone).label: Christ the King Cathedral
Christ the King Cathedral (Gaborone).description: Christ the King Cathedral is a Roman Catholic church in Gaborone, Botswana. It is the mother church of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Gaborone. The current bishop is Valentine Tsamma Seane. Wikipedia
